
Connector for EBYTE E22-xxxTxxU/D devices, for USB module (Linux) and DIP module (Linux/ESP32).

Tested with E22-900T22U (USB), E22-900T22D (DIP) and E22-900T30D (DIP) devices, see specs directory.

Should work for entire family: 230, 400 and 900 frequency and 20, 22, 30 and 33 dbm power variants.

The E22 is the more featured product, compared to the E220 and E32 versions, which would also work
with this connector with some minor modifications (the E220 lacks the NETID configuration field, 
making it one byte shorter). Both E220 and E32 lack repeater functionality. E32 also lacks RSSI.

E22 is based on the new Semtech SX1262, and E220 on the older Semtech SX1276. E32 is based on "low
cost" Semtech LLCC68.

Further information at https://www.cdebyte.com/Module-SPISOCUART-SX12.

Linux version has command line testers for USB and DIP and a 'tomqtt' version with udev and systemd
configuration files.

Greenfield implementation, not based upon others: see LICENSE (Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike).

NOTE: for the USB variant, you will to enable "Software Mode Switching", which is disabled by default,
otherwise the Connector is not able to configure the device. You need to hold the touch switch for more
than 1.5s to force the device into configuration mode, then start the Connector, which will then set
(and persist) "Software Mode Switching" so that manual intervention is no longer required.

